            That paragraph points out that if the arbitrator resigns and is sued for his fees, he is not protected from a breach of contract action under the immunity clause, Clause 29; but, on the other hand, if he is removed by the court he has the benefit of immunity under Clause 29.</p><p>
            That is an anomaly and I wonder whether my noble and learned friend is able to help us with his consideration of that paragraph in the report?
          </p>
