      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_19gc' title='Col. 19GC &mdash; HL Deb 28 February 1996 vol 569 c19GC' name='column_19gc' href='#column_19gc' rel='bookmark'>19GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0569P0-06262'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0569P0_19960228_GCR_150' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 70 [<span class="italic">Challenge or appeal: supplementary provisions</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0569P0-06263'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0569P0_19960228_GCR_151' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Fraser of Carmyllie</span> moved Amendment No. 16:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0569P0-06264'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0569P0_19960228_GCR_152' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
